  "prompt": "How can I make High quality video with small file size?",
  "response": "To create high-quality videos with a small file size, consider these techniques:\n\n1. Video Encoding Settings\n- Use efficient codecs like H.264/H.265\n- Adjust bitrate carefully\n- Use variable bitrate (VBR)\n- Choose appropriate resolution\n\n2. Compression Tools\n- HandBrake (free, open-source)\n- Adobe Media Encoder\n- FFmpeg\n- DaVinci Resolve\n\n3. Optimization Techniques\n- Lower frame rate (24-30 fps)\n- Reduce resolution\n- Use two-pass encoding\n- Limit color depth\n- Remove unnecessary metadata\n\n4. Export Settings\n- Choose H.264/H.265 codec\n- Target reasonable bitrate (e.g., 5-10 Mbps)\n- Select medium to slow encoding preset\n- Use constant quality setting\n\n5. Advanced Techniques\n- Use motion-compensated compression\n- Utilize GPU encoding\n- Apply noise reduction\n- Optimize keyframe intervals\n\n6. Software Recommendations\n- Adobe Premiere Pro\n- Final Cut Pro\n- Vegas Pro\n- DaVinci Resolve\n\n7. Streaming Optimization\n- Use adaptive bitrate streaming\n- Create multiple quality versions\n\nEach technique balances quality and file size differently, so experiment to find your ideal settings.",
